tion.\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 896, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 846, \"end\": 860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasatch_County,_Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999999942233444, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wasatch County\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasatch_County,_Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasatch_County,_Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Councilmember and light rail advocate Bill Ciraco said any solution for state Route 248 should be aimed at reducing the number of vehicles in town.\", \"from\": 898, \"to\": 1045, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think it goes to everyone's quality of life, everyone that lives along those entry corridors,\\\" Ciraco said.\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1157, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's not really engine noise, so like electric vehicles are not going to change it much.\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's road noise, it's wheels on road.\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1285, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If we think about getting people out of cars and into more dense forms of transportation, that helps keep the road more local, more rural.\\\"\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Councilmember Ed Parigian said he's against any expansion of the road.\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1497, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Parigian said he'd like to increase park and ride options and bus service frequency.\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1582, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To me that's the key to getting people on the bus,\\\" Parigian said.\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They do not have a half-hour wait, or even a 20-minute wait.\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1713, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe it needs to be 10 minutes.\\\"\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1747, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Along with other members of the council, Park City Mayor Nann Worel expressed interest in working with the school district to reduce daily congestion on state Route 248.\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1790, \"end\": 1799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Park_City_Mountain_Resort\", \"score\": 0.9999819338008235, \"rank\": 1.8066525642577245e-05, \"text\": \"Park City\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Park_City_Mountain_Resort\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Park_City_Mountain_Resort\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The council decided to pursue federal funding for future projects as they develop specific plans.\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 2017, \"entities\": []}]}"